    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 10-SI SERIES, TYPE 116 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - DIODE TRIO CHECK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="2">
        <title>DIODE TRIO CHECK</title>
        <para>The diode trio is identified in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0801206">Figure 6</hotlnk>. To check the diode trio, remove it from the end frame assembly
            by removing three nuts and attaching screws. Remove the stator assembly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0801206" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0801206" filename="../figg08/G0801206.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>View Inside End Frame</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RECTIFIER BRIDGE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CAPACITOR</callout1>
                <callout1>3. INSULATING WASHERS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. DIODE TRIO</callout1>
                <callout1>5. ATTACHING NUTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The insulating washer on the screw is assembled over the top of the diode trio connector during
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Connect an ohmmeter having a 1-1/2 volt cell to the single connector and to one of the three connectors (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0801207">Figure 7</hotlnk>). Observe the reading, using a lower range scale, (Rx1 or Rx10).
            Then reverse the ohmmeter leads to the same two connectors. If both readings are the same, replace the diode
            trio. A good diode trio will give one high and one low reading.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0801207" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0801207" filename="../figg08/G0801207.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Diode Trio Check</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OHMMETER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SINGLE CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>3. THREE (3) CONNECTORS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Repeat this same test between the single connector and each of the other two connectors. Also, connect the
            ohmmeter to each pair of the three connectors. If any reading is zero, replace the diode trio.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
